bib.title: Scattering of 23.7 MeV alpha-particles on the N-14 and O-16 nuclei.

free_txt: English translation was added. Sub 006 was
Optical model analysis with l-dependence of optical
Three semiconductor detectors were used for the
registration of alpha-particles. One of them was set
under 30 degrees to the beam. It served as a monitor.
A gas target was used. The gas tank was separated
from the vacuum system of the experimental chamber
by the aluminum foil of 7 microns thickness and by the
lavsan film of 2 microns thickness. The energy waste
in the input foil and in gas under work pressure of
100 torr decreases the beam energy from 24.2 MeV
to (23.7+ -0.2) MeV. The gas was get from liquid oxygen
and nitrogen. The impurities were lower than 4%.
